    "This strategy lies between data-level and algorithm-level strategies.",
    "They can operate at the data level by assigning costs to individual instances or at the algorithm level by incorporating cost considerations into the learning process (López et al. 2013; Fernández et al. 2018).",
    "• Ensemble-based strategies combine multiple base learners to create a more accurate and robust classification model.",
    "These strategies can be adapted to handle imbalanced datasets in two ways.",
    "Firstly, the ensemble learning algorithm can be modified at the data level, enabling preprocessing steps to be performed on the data before the learning stage of each classifier (López et al. 2013; Fernández et al. 2018)."
